.SH "NAME"
Dist::Zilla::Plugin::FileFinder::Filter \- filter matches from other FileFinders
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 6.010
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
In your \fIdist.ini\fR:
.PP
.Vb 4
\&  [FileFinder::Filter / MyFiles]
\&  finder = :InstallModules ; find files from :InstallModules
\&  finder = :ExecFiles      ; or :ExecFiles
\&  skip  = ignore           ; that don\*(Aqt have "ignore" in the path
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
FileFinder::Filter is a FileFinder that
selects files by filtering the selections of other FileFinders.
.PP
You specify one or more FileFinders to generate the initial list of
files.  Any file whose pathname matches any of the \f(CW\*(C`skip\*(C'\fR regexs is
removed from that list.
.SH "ATTRIBUTES"
.IX Header "ATTRIBUTES"
.SS "finder"
.IX Subsection "finder"
A FileFinder to supply the initial list of files.
May occur multiple times.
.SS "skip"
.IX Subsection "skip"
The pathname must \fInot\fR match any of these regular expressions.
May occur multiple times.
